edd Fychan]]\n  |votes      = 2,802\n  |percentage = 8.3\n  |change     = +1.3\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Nick Colbourne\n  |votes      = 2,407\n  |percentage = 7.1\n  |change     = \u22125.2\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = UK Independence Party\n  |candidate  = David W. L. Rowlands \n  |votes      = 1,128\n  |percentage = 3.3\n  |change     = +0.4\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = National Front (UK)\n  |candidate  = Milton Ellis\n  |votes      = 384\n  |percentage = 1.1\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link\n  |party      = Independent (politician)\n  |candidate  = Bruce Lawson\n  |votes      = 324\n  |percentage = 1.0\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box majority\n  |votes      = 1,184\n  |percentage = 3.5\n  |change     = ''N/A''\n}}\n{{Election box turnout\n  |votes      = 33,813\n  |percentage = 69.4\n  |change     = +3.1\n}}\n{{Election box registered electors|\n  |reg. electors = 48,730\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link\n  |winner     = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |loser      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |swing      = +13.2\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\nnote: The David Rowlands who stood here is different from the [[David Rowlands (Welsh politician)|David Rowlands]] who stood in [[Newport East (UK Parliament constituency)|Newport East]] at this election for UKIP.\n\n====Elections in the 2000s====\n{{Election box begin|title=[[2005 United Kingdom general election|General election 2005]]: Montgomeryshire<ref name=electoralcalculus2005>{{cite web|title=Election Data 2005|url=http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2005ob.txt|publisher=[[Electoral Calculus]]|accessdate=18 October 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015054249/http://www.electoralcalculus.co.uk/electdata_2005ob.txt|archivedate=15 October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/shared/vote2005/